It was Election Day (presidential primary and special election for this district) when I stopped by, and naturally I encouraged the employees there to vote. The young man seemed interested in what I had to say, but the older woman with glasses scoffed. It wasn't necessarily rude but rather frustrating. To that woman: Please consider participating in the political process, if you are eligible. Implying that your vote doesn't matter is exactly what "they" want you to think. Do not despair.
